summary: An Ordinance amending Section 1, of Ordinance No. 4072, entitled "An Ordinance granting unto Frye-Bruhn Company, a Washington corporation, its successors and assigns, the right and authority to locate, lay down, construct, maintain and operate a railway consisting of one track, in along, upon and over certain public streets, alleys and premises in the City of Seattle." Approved January 22nd, 1896.
